---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Unit Guide | Mechanics" description="Canonical formulas and assumptions.">
  <div class="card">
    <h1 style="margin-top:0;">Mechanics and formulas</h1>
    <p style="color:var(--muted); line-height:1.6;">
      This page is the canon for how the site calculates derived stats.
      The goal is consistency across every chart, not perfection in every edge case.
    </p>

    <hr class="sep" />

    <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Base DPS</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--muted); line-height:1.6;">
      Base DPS is calculated from base stats as damage divided by cooldown.
      If a unit has multi-hit, splash, chain, summons, or ramping, you can add an additional “Effective DPS” rule later,
      but the base DPS stays the simplest common denominator.
    </p>

    <hr class="sep" />

    <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Level scaling</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--muted); line-height:1.6;">
      Level 1 uses the listed base stats. Level N uses base + (N - 1) × per-level gain.
      The unit pages let you preview the resulting stats by appending <code>?level=</code>.
    </p>

    <hr class="sep" />

    <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Status effects</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--muted); line-height:1.6;">
      Stun is displayed as duration per hit. “Stun uptime” is not currently computed.
      Poison is displayed as total damage per application when duration is unknown.
      Burn that scales with enemy HP should be documented as a percent and optionally given an example HP target.
    </p>

    <hr class="sep" />

    <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Versioning</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--muted); line-height:1.6;">
      Every update should include a date and the game version on the Patch notes page.
      If an assumption changes, update this page first, then regenerate charts.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
